WorkItem.Description:
Issue workitem #35 seems to be closed, but I still see it in the 0.8.3 compiler.
http://typescript.codeplex.com/workitem/35

The bug appears if running the compiler from node, but you don't see the error if running from tsc.exe.

It's not a huge issue because of the workaround, but the __proto__ field is common in existing javaScript code and it's not obvious what is causing it.
WorkItem.Summary: __proto__ Internal Compiler Error bug still there in 8.3

Comments.Message: We've re-opened the bug internally, and see how it goes :)
